    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#charAt(int)\" rel=\"noreferrer\">.charAt(int)</a> function with Strings to retrieve the char value at any index. If you want to convert the String to a char array, try calling <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#toCharArray()\" rel=\"noreferrer\">.toCharArray()</a> on the String.</p>\n\n<pre><code>String g = \"line\";\nchar c = g.charAt(0);  // returns 'l'\nchar[] c_arr = g.toCharArray(); // returns a length 4 char array ['l','i','n','e']\n</code></pre>\n"
