      "body" : "@Vlad He did ask for a number, because that&#39;s what a <code>char</code> is, just like <code>int</code> and <code>double</code>. He even gave the example <code>String</code> &quot;123&quot;. and who says you can&#39;t convert a <code>char</code> to a <code>String</code> with a length larger than one, and back? Try it yourself with <code>char c = 123</code> : <code>String.valueOf((int) c).equals(&quot;123&quot;)</code> returns <code>true</code>."
