    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you want to parse a String to a char, whereas the String object represent more than one character, you just simply use the following expression:\n<em>char c = (char) Integer.parseInt(s)</em>.\nWhere <em>s</em> equals the String you want to parse. Most people forget that char's represent a 16-bit number, and thus can be a part of <strong>any</strong> numerical expression :)</p>\n"
