    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/10/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#charAt(int)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">.charAt(int)</a> function with Strings to retrieve the char value at any index. If you want to convert the String to a char array, try calling <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/10/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#toCharArray()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">.toCharArray()</a> on the String. If the string is 1 character long, just take that character by calling .charAt(0) (or .First() in C#).</p>\n"
